          "date": "2024-06-26 09:00:12.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-17323 lib: l_wait_event occasionally clears sigpending",
        "message": "LU-17323 lib: l_wait_event occasionally clears sigpending\n\nl_wait_event() calls recalc_sigpending() which can clear\nTIF_SIGPENDING if a signal was processed in a parallel thread\nand is no longer pending.\n\nIf this l_wait_event() is called from the fork cleanup part,\nit's possible that fork() is going to return ERESTARTNOINTR,\nhowever, if TIF_SIGPENDING is cleared, this errno can leak\nto userspace while a syscall restart is expected.\n\nMake sure TIF_SIGPENDING is restored if it was set on entry\nto l_wait_event().\n\nChange-Id: I490af67e6cf53d0521dd8d9c44d78bdd44934001\nSigned-off-by: Andrew Perepechko <andrew.perepechko@hpe.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master",
      "description": "Edit commit message"
    }
  },
